import os, sys, glob, shutil, re, sysconfig, traceback, io, subprocess

def spCall(cmd,*args,**kwds):
    r = subprocess.call(
            cmd,
            stderr = subprocess.STDOUT,
            stdout = subprocess.DEVNULL if kwds.pop('dropOutput',False) else None,
            timeout = kwds.pop('timeout',3600),
            )
    if verbose>=3:
        infoline('%r --> %s' % (' '.join(cmd),r), pfx='!!!!!' if r else '#####', add=False)
    return r

# Data dependencies:
# - subprocess: imported at top
# - cmd: argument to spCall
# - kwds: argument to spCall
# - subprocess.STDOUT, subprocess.DEVNULL: from subprocess
# - verbose: set by 'verbose = specialOption('--verbose',ceq=True)' (global)
# - infoline: defined above
